https://www.jamescoyle.net/how-to/1503-create-your-first-docker-container

Build image with name
	docker build -t <image_name> .

Create container and get into it	
	docker run --name <container_name> -it <container_id> bash 
	Note: On exit container will stop. 

Start existing container 
	docker start <NameContainer>

Stop existing container 
	docker stop <NameContainer>

To login to a container
docker exec -it <mycontainer> bash

Show all images
	docker image ls
Remove image
	docker image rm <ImageName|ImageID>
Show all containers
	docker ps -a
Remove container
	docker container rm <ContainerName|ContainerID>
